-- Colombian Stocks: Tableros & Maderas, Ecopetrol, Petrominerales
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-02-29T16:01:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/colombian-stocks-tableros-maderas-ecopetrol-petrominerales.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:48 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 1.3 percent to 14,914.74, while the
Colcap Index gained 0.7 percent to 1,719.97.  Tableros & Maderas de Caldas SA  (TABLEMA CB) rose 1 percent
to 10.3 pesos. The wood products maker’s 2011 sales rose 18
percent from a year ago to 109 billion pesos ($61.6 million),
according to a regulatory filing. Profit fell 29 percent from a
year ago to 7.1 billion pesos.  The company had costs related to construction of a medium-
density fiberboard plant, and “once it starts running in May,
the company will reflect a higher level of sales, and more
stable cost structure,” Interbolsa SA analysts including Jorge Zuniga said an e-mailed report today. Interbolsa rates the stock
a buy.  Oil companies  advanced as crude gained as much as 0.8
percent in  New York .  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  ,  Colombia ’s largest oil company,
rose 1.3 percent to 5,060 pesos, a record high.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMGC)  (PMGC CB), a Calgary-based company that
explores for and produces oil in Colombia, gained 3.2 percent to
32,400 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
